A general view of the MTN 8 trophy. JOHANNESBURG - The MTN 8 final between Highlands Park and Supersport United will be played at Orlando Stadium on Saturday, October 05. United reached their third consecutive top 8 final by defeating their arch-rivals Mamelodi Sundowns 3-1 on aggregate. READ: SuperSport eyeing MTN8 glory Both teams played 1-all in the first leg but United came strong in the second leg to defeat Sundowns 2-0 at Lucas Masterpiece Moripe Stadium on Wednesday night. Their opponents, Highlands, have reached their first-ever final since it gained promotion to the PSL two seasons ago. Matsatsantsa A Pitori will be hoping to lift the cup this time around having lost in the finals last year to Cape Town City.